# Commit And Push Default

The user wants completed work in this repository committed and pushed by default.

- After finishing requested edits and relevant verification, commit all relevant non-secret changes and push the current branch.
- Include new files that are part of the work; leave unrelated generated artifacts or local noise uncommitted.
- Never commit likely secrets, credentials, private keys, `.env` files, or local machine-only config.
- Do not use destructive git operations or force-push unless the user explicitly asks for that in the current conversation.
- If verification cannot run, still commit and push when the changes are otherwise complete, and clearly state what was blocked.
